item.title: Annie add a quote by Chelsea Cain
item.description: "Something about the way she moves through the world does not lend itself to the care of fragile objects." -- Chelsea Cain

item.title: Annie add a quote by Franny Billingsley
item.description: "It is true that I can trip over anything and nothing – a speck of dust, a patch of sunlight, an idea. I move through life like a person with one eye, through a landscape that looks flat, but is really tricked out with hidden depths and shallows. It didn’t use to be so, but no matter. I navigate the world well enough in my own way." -- Franny Billingsley

item.title: Annie add a quote by Franny Billingsley
item.description: "It's one thing to keep secrets. It's quite another to lie." -- Franny Billingsley
